## The Design Thinking Process

<img src="https://images.code.org/af347ab3e6a799250df9c3301d93674c-image-1714589887029.png" alt="design process graph of the cycle" width="300px" style="border-radius:10px; float:right; margin: 0 0 40px 40px;">



#### In this project students will work through the **Design Thinking Process**. The process involves five steps that teams use to understand users, challenge assumptions, redefine problems, and create innovative solutions. 

### Cyclical Design Process 

#### Students will use this process throughout this unit as they work towards developing a prototype for a computer vision product. It involves understanding users, defining problems, brainstorming solutions, creating prototypes, and testing them while emphasizing a **user-centric mindset**.

### Why use this process?

#### By practicing these steps, students will learn to continuously improve their ideas and ultimately develop their own prototypes. This cyclical process helps students build creativity and problem-solving skills in a practical, hands-on way.


## Up Next!
#### Explore the steps students will go through when completing their projects.




